```suggestion
Assume `pres : Algebra.Presentation R S` is a presentation of `S` as an `R`-algebra.
```

```suggestion
that is obtained from a presentation of `S` as an `R`-algebra. -/
```

```suggestion
/-! We obtain here a few compatibilities which allow to compare the two sequences
`(pres.rels ‚Üí‚ÇÄ S) ‚Üí (pres.vars ‚Üí‚ÇÄ S) ‚Üí Œ©[S‚ÅÑR]` and
`pres.toExtension.Cotangent ‚Üí‚Çó[S] pres.toExtension.CotangentSpace ‚Üí Œ©[S‚ÅÑR]`.
```

```suggestion
/-- The canonical map `(pres.rels ‚Üí‚ÇÄ S) ‚Üí‚Çó[S] pres.toExtension.Cotangent`. -/
noncomputable def hom‚ÇÅ : (pres.rels ‚Üí‚ÇÄ S) ‚Üí‚Çó[S] pres.toExtension.Cotangent :=
  Finsupp.linearCombination S (fun r ‚Ü¶ Extension.Cotangent.mk ‚ü®pres.relation r, by simp‚ü©)
```
I think the idea is to prefer the specialized `Extension.Cotangent` API over `Ideal.Cotangent`. Otherwise you fall out of the `Extension.Cotangent` simp lemmas. (see below)

```suggestion
  simp only [hom‚ÇÅ, Finsupp.linearCombination_single, one_smul, differentialsRelations,
    Basis.repr_symm_apply, Extension.cotangentComplex_mk]
```
works if you change the definition of `hom_1` as above.

```suggestion
  simp_rw [‚Üê differentialsRelations_G, ‚Üê differentialsRelations_R, Module.Relations.map_single]
```
The alternative to this is removing `@[simp]` from `differentialsRelations_{G,R}` and replace occurrences of `pres.vars` and `pres.rels` with `differentialsRelations.G` and `differentialsRelations.R` respectively.
Removing the `simps` attribute is not an option here, but I have found another way to remove the `erw` (this type of `erw` will be solved by the expected `dsimp%` elaborator).

pullRequest.title: feat(Algebra/Module): a presentation of an algebra induces a presentation of the module of differentials
